# Code Organization

## Split large components

File >150 LOC or ≥2 internal subcomponents → promote to a folder with a
barrel. Import paths stay the same.

```
ConfigDrawer/
├── index.ts          # re-exports public API (component + props types)
├── ConfigDrawer.tsx  # shell
├── ConfigTabPanel.tsx
└── RunDetailPanel.tsx
```

File-private subcomponents (e.g. `StatusRow`) stay inside the parent file —
don't export unless reused elsewhere.

## Extract pure helpers to `utils/`

Pure functions (formatters, parsers, predicates, math) must NOT sit at the
bottom of a component file.

- Feature-scoped → `src/pages/<feature>/utils/<topic>.ts`
- App-wide      → `src/lib/utils.ts`

Each `utils/` folder has an `index.ts` barrel. One file per topic
(`format.ts`, `graph.ts`, `validation.ts`). Helpers must be pure (no React,
no state, no JSX) — anything with a hook/ref/JSX is a component or belongs
under `hooks/`.

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ pure helper at bottom of component file
export function RunDetailPanel() { /* ... */ }
function formatTime(ts: number) { /* ... */ }

// ✅ helper in utils, component imports it
// pages/workflow/utils/format.ts
export function formatTime(ts: number) { /* ... */ }
// pages/workflow/components/ConfigDrawer/RunDetailPanel.tsx
import { formatTime } from "../../utils";
```

## Checklist

- Component file ≤ ~250 LOC
- No pure helpers below JSX
- Every multi-file folder has `index.ts`
- Cross-feature helpers live in `src/lib/`
